## ğŸ—„ï¸ Database Setup (MySQL)

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Open **MySQL Command Line Client**
You should see:
mysql>


### 2ï¸âƒ£ Create database
```sql
CREATE DATABASE college;
USE college;

3ï¸âƒ£ Create students table
CREATE TABLE students (
  id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(150) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
  dob DATE NOT NULL,
  department VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  phone VARCHAR(15) NOT NULL,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

ğŸ“¥ Sample Data Insertion
INSERT INTO students (name, email, dob, department, phone) VALUES
('Arjun Reddy', 'arjun.reddy@gmail.com', '2001-08-15', 'CSE', '9876543210'),
('Sneha Sharma', 'sneha.sharma@gmail.com', '2002-03-22', 'ECE', '9123456780'),
('Rahul Verma', 'rahul.verma@gmail.com', '2001-11-05', 'ME', '9988776655');


Verify:

SELECT * FROM students;

ğŸš€ Backend Setup (Node.js + Express)
1ï¸âƒ£ Install dependencies
npm install

2ï¸âƒ£ Configure database connection (db.js)
const mysql = require("mysql2");

const db = mysql.createConnection({
  host: "localhost",
  user: "root",
  password: "",       // Add your MySQL password if any
  database: "college"
});

db.connect(err => {
  if (err) {
    console.error("Database connection failed:", err.message);
    return;
  }
  console.log("Database connected");
});

module.exports = db;

â–¶ï¸ Run the Server
node server.js

Expected output:
Database connected
Server running on http://localhost:3000

ğŸ”— API Endpoints
â• Register Student

POST /students

Request Body (JSON):

{
  "name": "Kiran Kumar",
  "email": "kiran@gmail.com",
  "dob": "2001-01-30",
  "department": "CSE",
  "phone": "9012345678"
}

ğŸ“„ Get All Students

GET /students

URL:

